column5: Had to take advantage of today's weather so wife and I decided on Cliff Lake.Tried a couple of spots for trout but those didn't pan out.We were close to a couple of great walleye spots and tried them and they were bang on.Some of the most beautifull walleyes come out of trout waters and Cliff doesn't disappoint.Really got in to them.Mostly to big to keep but managed 2 limits of nice eaters.Ended up getting 2 muskies also and a few bass.Water temp at 57F.Spotlock on the edge of a drop off and they couldn't resist the jigs and minnows we sent down ,even did very good an a vibrato.Calm day for most part but a breezy east went came in afternoon.Fall foliage is turning colors.
Looks like a great day to be on the lake, nice fish John.
Thx.nice to have the option of picking nice days.
Way to go Ms. Sylvia!! Nice fish guys. If I had only stayed one day longer this trip .LOL. PjShorthorn
Looks like a great day on the lake.
Couple of pics that say it all from yesterday's adventure.Todays weather not so nice.
beautiful photos! I was up there one year ago today for 10 days. Stunningly beautiful this time of year. No bugs, no boats, chilly evenings by the fire! Can't beat it!!
Yes to everything mentioned.Decent weather next week so might get another day there yet.
